TITLE: Basic Rule Structure in Rules DSL
DESCRIPTION: The fundamental syntax structure for defining a rule in openHAB Rules DSL. Each rule requires a unique name, one or more trigger conditions, and a script block containing the actions to execute when triggered.
SOURCE: https://github.com/openhab/openhab-docs/blob/main/configuration/rules-dsl.md#2025-04-09_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: java
