TITLE: Implementing Concurrency Guard in OpenHAB Rules (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to protect against concurrent execution of rule code using a ReentrantLock. This pattern is useful when rules might be triggered simultaneously by UI events.
SOURCE: https://github.com/openhab/openhab-docs/blob/main/configuration/rules-dsl.md#2025-04-09_snippet_29

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import java.util.concurrent.locks.ReentrantLock

val ReentrantLock lock  = new ReentrantLock()

rule ConcurrentCode
when
    Item Dummy received update
then
    lock.lock()
    try {
        // do stuff
    } finally{
        lock.unlock()
    }
end
```

