TITLE: Defining Basic Rule Structure in YAML
DESCRIPTION: This YAML snippet shows the structure of a basic rule in openHAB, including triggers, conditions, and actions. It demonstrates how to set up a rule that turns on an Item when certain conditions are met.
SOURCE: https://github.com/openhab/openhab-docs/blob/main/tutorials/getting_started/rules_basic.md#2025-04-09_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
triggers:
  - id: "1"
    configuration:
      itemName: vCloudiness
    type: core.ItemStateChangeTrigger
conditions:
  - id: "2"
    configuration:
      itemName: vCloudiness
      operator: GE
      state: 50 %
    type: core.ItemStateCondition
  - id: "3"
    configuration:
      itemName: vIsCloudy
      operator: "!="
      state: ON
    type: core.ItemStateCondition
actions:
  - id: "4"
    configuration:
      itemName: vIsCloudy
      command: ON
    type: core.ItemCommandAction
configuration: {}
type: core.rules:rule
```

