TITLE: Parameterized Custom Light List Widget in openHAB
DESCRIPTION: This YAML demonstrates a parameterized custom light list widget that uses properties to make the widget reusable. It accepts a title and item parameter, and updates the icon color and widget title dynamically based on these parameters.
SOURCE: https://github.com/openhab/openhab-docs/blob/main/tutorials/getting_started/custom_widgets.md#2025-04-09_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
uid: test_light_list
props:
  parameterGroups: []
  parameters:
    - name: title
      label: Widget Title
      type: TEXT
      description: Used as the label for the widget.
    - name: item
      label: Item
      type: TEXT
      context: item
      description: The item to control
tags:
  - lights
  - list
component: oh-toggle-item
config:
  icon: f7:lightbulb
  iconColor: '=(items[props.item].state == "ON") ? "yellow" : "gray"'
  title: =props.title
  color: '=(items[props.item].state == "ON") ? "yellow" : "gray"'
  item: =props.item
```

